<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 6:21AM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...Areas of Dense Fog for Early Morning Drivers Across the
Ranchlands...
The combination of recently moistened ground from rainfall
associated with Tropical Storm Harold on Tuesday with clear skies
and calm winds this morning has allowed ground and field fog to
form across the Brush Country in Jim Hogg County through the
Brooks and Kenedy ranchlands, as well as farms of Willacy and
northern Hidalgo.
Visibility has been reduced to one quarter mile or less in some
areas, and will continue to be reduced through 8 to 830 AM before
burning off quickly. Motorists should remain alert to rapidly
dropping visibility and reduce speeds, use fog lights or low beam
headlights, and keep plenty of distance between vehicles.</description>
